quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  43,1,"Ha'. Mim."
  43,2,"By the Clear Book;"
  43,3,"verily We have made it an Arabic Qur'an that you may understand."{1},footnotes:1:1
  43,4,"Indeed it is transcribed in the Original Book with Us; sublime and full of wisdom."{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  43,5,"Should We divert this Good Counsel from you because you are a people immersed in extravagance?"{1},footnotes:1:1
  43,6,"How many a Prophet did We send to the earlier peoples!"
  43,7,"Yet never did a Prophet come to them but they mocked him."{1},footnotes:1:1
  43,8,"We utterly destroyed them although they were greater in might than these. The examples of ancient peoples have gone before."{1},footnotes:1:1
  43,9,"Yet if you were to ask them: “Who created the heavens and the earth?” they will certainly say: “The All-Mighty, the All-Knowing has created them.”"
  43,10,"He it is Who made this earth for you a cradle and made in it pathways for you that you may find the way to your destination;"{1}{2}{3},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2,footnotes:3:3